of 10,000 to 12,000 meters per second. A chemical orion<br>
using detonations behind an intertial plate can achieve an<br>
effective specific impulse of 500 to 600 seconds assumimg<br>
a collimation factor of 50%. If the explosives were detonated<br>
inside of a chamber however a specific impulse of 1000<br>
to 1200 seconds for chemical high explosive powered orions might be reached. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/utmayes1999.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tmayes1999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/3/02 8:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~projectorion/ezboard/posticons/3.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hot Rods.</span><hr size=1> Chemical orions would carry their fuel onboard in a magizine<br>
